      • validateCLIArgumentsForServerStart

        public static void validateCLIArgumentsForServerStart(java.lang.String[] arguments)
                                               throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Validate CLI arguments for the server starting. The arguments are valid, if:
        (1) there are exactly REQUIRED_CLI_ARGUMENT_NUMBER number of arguments, and
        (2) the arguments at the position CLI_KVCLIENT_PORT_INDEX, CLI_KVSERVER_PORT_INDEX, CLI_KVECS_PORT_INDEX are valid ports, and
        (3) the argument at the position CLI_CACHE_SIZE_INDEX is a valid cache size, and
        (4) the argument at the position CLI_DISPLACEMENT_STRATEGY_INDEX is a valid displacement strategy, and
        (5) the argument at the position CLI_LOG_LEVEL_INDEX is a valid log level, and
        (7) the argument at the position CLI_LOADBALANCER_IP_INDEX is a valid IP address, and
        (7) the argument at the position CLI_LOADBALANCER_PORT_INDEX is a valid port
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a validation error occurs

        public static void validateStartArguments(java.lang.String[] arguments,

        (1) it does not have any arguments, and
